1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with network information flow and specifically mentions wireless networks, which falls under this category. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses a max-flow min-cut theorem, which is a fundamental concept in information theory. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper mentions small world topologies, which are commonly found in social networks. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper involves proving a theorem and deriving bounds, which are typical topics in this category. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with network connectivity and flow, which can be viewed as a control problem in some contexts.
